{
  "title": "If God Had Not Been on Our Side",
  "key": "f♯ minor",
  "key_root": "F#",
  "mode": "minor",
  "meter": "4/4",
  "bpm": 100,
  "words": "Martin Luther, 1524.  Translation composite",
  "music": "from Walter&#39;s Geistliche Gesangbüchlein, 1524 Michael Praetorius, 1610",
  "tune": "Wär Gott nicht mit uns diese Zeit (1524)",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "If God had not been on our side And had not come to aid us, The foes with all their pow&#39;r and pride Would surely have dismayed us; For we, His flock, would have to fear The threat of men both far and near Who rise in might against us.",
    "v2": "Their furious wrath, did God permit, Would surely have consumed us And as a deep and yawning pit With life and limb entombed us. Like men o&#39;er whom dark waters roll Their wrath would have engulfed our soul And, like a flood, o&#39;erwhelmed us.",
    "v3": "Blest be the Lord, who foiled their threat That they could not devour us; Our souls, like birds, escaped their net, They could not overpow&#39;r us. The snare is broken we are free! Our help is ever, Lord, in Thee, Who madest earth and heaven."
  },
